Doesn't pressing on it make it hurt more?

00:47:28.680 --> 00:47:30.850
- That's the stuff. - Doesn't it hurt more?

00:47:31.320 --> 00:47:34.690
Inviting people over for a housewarming party...

00:47:35.290 --> 00:47:38.860
I thought it was just a thing you do since others do, but I was wrong.

00:47:40.560 --> 00:47:41.760
What do you mean?

00:47:43.230 --> 00:47:47.340
It feels like a way to show people, "Hey, look, I'm doing well."

00:47:47.900 --> 00:47:51.540
And it's like promising yourself you'll live even better from now on.

00:47:52.980 --> 00:47:56.550
I'm not exactly sure what "living well" means, but...

00:47:57.950 --> 00:48:01.120
Living well...

00:48:02.550 --> 00:48:03.890
Take a towel, for instance.

00:48:04.790 --> 00:48:10.060
When it's all fluffy and soft, you use it for your face.

00:48:10.390 --> 00:48:15.560
Once it gets frayed and rough, you use it for your feet.

00:48:16.700 --> 00:48:20.640
And when the stains won't come out, and it's gotten limp,

00:48:21.640 --> 00:48:23.570
you turn it into a rag.

00:48:25.040 --> 00:48:28.110
I guess living like that...

00:48:29.610 --> 00:48:31.550
That's what it means to live well, I suppose.

00:48:35.950 --> 00:48:37.450
Thank you for coming.

00:48:40.560 --> 00:48:41.760
I really mean it.

00:48:46.760 --> 00:48:47.760
Ja Yeong.

