we have an opening for a liberal arts lecturer,

00:52:39.660 --> 00:52:42.059
but I need to see the department head.

00:52:42.060 --> 00:52:44.070
It's policy, but I'll contact you.

00:52:44.200 --> 00:52:48.270
- Yes, thank you, sir. - All right.

00:52:51.670 --> 00:52:52.670
Jin Ho.

00:52:53.880 --> 00:52:55.340
Are you still mad at me?

00:52:57.210 --> 00:52:58.310
I'm not mad.

00:52:58.450 --> 00:53:01.720
A fire out here in the mountains would be a total disaster.

00:53:02.050 --> 00:53:04.020
You're right. That could have been a disaster.

00:53:05.650 --> 00:53:09.190
I guess I got carried away. I wasn't thinking straight.

00:53:10.360 --> 00:53:11.690
I'm so sorry.

00:53:12.030 --> 00:53:14.700
I promise, I'll be more careful from now on.

00:53:17.100 --> 00:53:21.540
I'm glad you like it here enough to lose your head over it.

00:53:24.410 --> 00:53:27.010
So does that mean you're not mad anymore?

00:53:28.510 --> 00:53:30.050
No. Still mad.

00:53:31.280 --> 00:53:33.210
- Come on. - Stop it. What are you doing?

00:53:37.050 --> 00:53:39.820
Hey, stop. I'm not over it, so just get away from me.

00:53:40.220 --> 00:53:41.220
Stop it.

00:53:46.360 --> 00:53:50.070
Do you know what's more important than the diamond for a proposal?

00:53:51.300 --> 00:53:52.330
What is it?

00:53:53.200 --> 00:53:54.200
Timing.

